<subSubSection pageId="42" pageNumber="43" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1437,1388,1991]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1928,1954]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chen &amp; Pu" authorityYear="1980" box="[607,715,1928,1955]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Adiscus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tibialis">
<emphasis box="[607,715,1928,1955]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">A. tibialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but distinguished by the coloration of body, lacking black spots. Its pronotum is broad and the lateral ridge of prosternum less bifurcate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
